        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 8:00AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 759 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Van Vleck, or near Bay City, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Jackson, Angleton, Bay City, Freeport, Clute, West Columbia,
Sweeny, Surfside Beach, Richwood, Brazoria, Jones Creek, Oyster
Creek, Holiday Lakes, Bailey's Prairie, Thompsons, Wild Peach
Village, Brazos Bend State Park, Markham, Van Vleck, and Boling-Iago.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
